Table 1. This LUT is used for the duty-cycle PM presented in Fig. 3, which is implemented in each node to respect ENO condition. The resolution of the wake-up period is set to 0.5s. The reference voltage VRef = 4V and k = 10. Following metrics are used to evaluate the performance of the system:
• Packet received Data-Rate (P DR) (bits/s) : It is deﬁned as the ratio between the size of the packet (128bits) and the average wake-up period.
• Packet Received Rate (P RR) (%) : the ratio between the total correctly received packet at the BS node and the total transmitted packet from all ED nodes.
• IDLT x and IDLRx (ms) : the average idle listening time at ED nodes and the BS node.
• ET x and ERx (µJ) : the average consumed energy at ED nodes and the BS node for one successful packet.
• EC (µJ): the average consumed energy for one successful packet from both BS and ED nodes.
6.2 Performance analysis
First, the simulation is performed on non-WUR platform which uses only the MRF CC2500 for wireless communication. Therefore, whenever the BS wakes up, MRF CC2500

